        <h2 id="coding">Type of coding used and rules</h2>
        <p>
            As this is a system which will often use same or similar elements, it is suitable to use a type of coding that divides web to components and variously combines them with each other.
        </p>

        <h3>Coding using BEM</h3>
        <p>
            BEM is a style of writing, which defines the rules for writing css
        </p>

        <ul class="list-main">
            <li class="list-main__item">
                two underscores "__" represent part of the component/element
            </li>
            <li class="list-main__item">
                two dash "--" represent modification of component
            </li>
            <li class="list-main__item">
                double signs are clear and developer will intuitively know senses of different classes given
            </li>
            <li class="list-main__item">
                one dash "-" represents separator in multi-word title
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="in-message in-message--error">
            It is important that you don\'t use just parts of the components (elements), you have to use the parent component.
        </p>


        <h3>Not using ID and !important for CSS</h3>
        <p>
            ID is an element with the highest priority in the CSS and that\'s why we are going to avoid it. Once we tie something to ID, we can beat it only with ID again or with !important. In real usage of SSS there had to be multiple adjustments of the same parts but on different places. If we use only classes and components we won\'t have these problems.
        </p>

        <p>
            Important is good sometimes, but once we tie important to something, we can beat it only with more specific write with another important. That\'s why we use the important only in utmost and logically excusable cases.
        </p>

        <p>
            The basic premis for coding in admin is, that mostly programmers will work with the code. That\'s why there is a bigger emphasis on helpers -
        </p>

        <h3>Writing of css characteristics according to priorities</h3>
        <p>
            At first we write underlying characteristics for element (position, float, display, width, ... ), then stylistic ones (font, color, background, ... )
        </p>

        <h3>Folders structure</h3>
        <ul class="list-main">
            <li class="list-main__item">
